  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins-on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1623670019887-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1623670019887-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1623670019887-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1623670019887-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1623670019887-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Soak the <strong>skewers</strong> in <strong>cold water</strong> (this stops them from burning whilst cooking!)</p><p>Deseed the <strong>pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</strong> </span>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>coriander</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1623670024338-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1623670024338-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1623670024338-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1623670024338-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1623670024338-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced pepper</strong>,<strong> sliced onion</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then cook for 2 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Once softened, reduce the heat to low and cook for 10 min or until caramelised</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1623670029448-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1623670029448-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1623670029448-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1623670029448-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1623670029448-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>halloumi</strong> in half lengthways (where the natural crease forms), and then cut each half into 2 strips so you end up with 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8] </span>strips</p><p>Sprinkle the <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika </strong>over the <strong>halloumi strips </strong>and pat it on all the sides until evenly coated</p><p>Carefully thread each <strong>coated</strong> <strong>halloumi strip</strong> onto a <strong>soaked</strong> <strong>skewer</strong> (try not to break them!) – these are your <strong>smoky halloumi skewers</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1623670035477-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1623670035477-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1623670035477-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1623670035477-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1623670035477-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once done, transfer the <strong>caramelised pepper & onion</strong> to a bowl (reserve the pan!)</p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> the<strong> red wine vinegar </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), the <strong>chopped coriander </strong>and 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>pepper</strong> <strong>& onion salsa</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1623670040719-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1623670040719-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1623670040719-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1623670040719-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1623670040719-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> smoky halloumi skewers</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>and cook for 6 min, turning so they brown on all sides</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1623670046302-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1623670046302-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
